sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K078000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: A fragment that encodes an enzyme involed in dioxin degradation
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: It is 2，2???，3-Trihydroxybiphenyl 1,2-dioxygenase, which catalyze the meta cleavage reaction, the second step, in the process of 4-chlorodibenzofuran degradation, from 2,2',3-Trihydroxybiphenyl to 2-Hydroxy-6-oxo-6-(2-hydroxyphenyl)-hexa-2,4-dienoate. The size is relatively small, 885bp.
